rComments:
Pros: Great prof, super interesting lectures, always available to help students, clear grading criteria. 
Cons: 2 large group projects, mandatory participation mark, lots of readings.
Even if you havent done the readings, just ask questions in class and all will be well participation mark wise.
Overall great prof but need to put in a lil effort. :)

Pretty unresponsive outside of class and the amount of group work where the mark is shared for a 3rd year class is honestly annoying and brought my mark down. Shes also super into in class participation. All that being said its a pretty standard if not repetitive sociology class thats an easy A if you get good group members.

This prof is nice, interesting to listen to, and responsive with feedback & questions. There isn't a crazy amount of work assigned which is nice, and the guest speakers are actually relevant to the material & interesting. Her grading is a bit odd and a little difficult but that's the only negative thing I can think of. I'd recommend this class!
